        html: "The Vaisseau 3008 was a temporary occupation project of a 3800m² building in the Placette district of Nîmes between 2020 and 2022. Formerly a Hôtel-Dieu and later the offices of Gard’s social services, the building hosted artists, designers, entrepreneurs, and associations for two years under the management of the Le Spot association. It was demolished in the summer of 2022."
